126
00:07:45,830 --> 00:07:47,230
You’re no longer bleeding, too.

127
00:07:47,230 --> 00:07:49,270
You’re just children.

128
00:07:49,270 --> 00:07:51,440
Why are you all hiding
in such a shabby temple?

129
00:07:52,720 --> 00:07:54,270
We’re schoolmates.

130
00:07:54,270 --> 00:07:57,000
We went to the same school
in our hometown.

131
00:07:57,390 --> 00:07:59,720
War broke out there.

132
00:07:59,720 --> 00:08:01,230
Our villagers ran away.

133
00:08:01,950 --> 00:08:04,110
Our parents and we lost each other.

134
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:07,760
Luckily, we met a kind teacher

135
00:08:07,760 --> 00:08:09,440
who led us forward.

136
00:08:09,440 --> 00:08:11,880
He said there was no war in the south.

137
00:08:11,880 --> 00:08:14,000
He had planned to take us to the south.

138
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:15,950
We found this shabby temple on our way

139
00:08:15,950 --> 00:08:17,950
as a temporary shelter.

140
00:08:17,950 --> 00:08:19,950
Where is the teacher, then?

141
00:08:19,950 --> 00:08:22,230
